The staff and management of Maternal-Child Specialists' Clinics, Ado-Ekiti has mourned the death of Dr. Oria Adebose. This was contained in a glowing tribute to the Late Dr. Oria, who was formerly with the Clinic and signed by Sir Ade-Ojo Idowu Pius (KSS). "It is with profound sadness that I mourn the loss of my professional daughter, Dr. Oria Adebose, whose untimely passing has left an unfillable void in my life and the lives of all who knew her. "I had the privilege of watching Adebose grow into an exceptional medical professional during her one-year compulsory youth service and subsequent three years as a medical officer at Maternal & Child Specialist Clinic (Mother and Child Hospital), Ado-Ekiti. Her dedication, compassion, and unwavering commitment to her patients earned her the respect and admiration of her colleagues and patients alike. "The entire staff of Maternal and Child Specialist Clinic, Ado-Ekiti, mourns her untimely departure, remembering the bright future she had ahead of her as a promising anaesthesiologist. My family and I are also grief-stricken, mourning the loss of our beloved Dr. Oria. "Adebose's passion for her craft led her to pursue Residency training in Anaesthesia at the prestigious Obafemi Awolowo University Teaching Hospital Complex (OAUTHC), Ile-Ife, where she rose through the ranks to become a Senior Registrar. Her thirst for knowledge and excellence inspired all who knew her. "Beyond her professional accomplishments, Adebose was a devoted Catholic, a lover of Christ, and a shining example of faith in action. Her kindness, empathy, and generosity inspired all who knew her. "I cherish the memories of our time together, including her visits to introduce her husband, David, and invite me to chair her wedding reception. My heart goes out to David, her loving husband, and her family, who are grieving her loss. May God grant them the fortitude to bear this irreparable loss. "I commiserate with the Chief Medical Director, HoD, consultants, and Resident Doctors in the department of anaesthesia, OAUTHC, Ile-Ife. I also extend my condolences to the members of the Association of Resident Doctors (ARD), OAUTHC, Ile-Ife, that she served as a vice president. "May God grant you all the fortitude to bear the painful death of a member of your staff and colleague. "As I struggle to come to terms with her passing, I am reminded of the immense impact Adebose had on my life and the lives of those around her. Her death is a devastating loss, and I will miss her dearly. "Rest in peace, dear Adebose. Your memory will live on in my heart, and your legacy will continue to inspire and motivate me. May God grant you eternal rest and comfort your loved ones in their time of grief."
